accent-color: The `accent-color` CSS property sets the accent color for user-interface controls generated by some elements.
background-image: The `background-image` CSS property sets one or more background images on an element.
mix-blend-mode: The mix-blend-mode CSS property sets how an element's content should blend with the content of the element's parent and the element's background.
width: The `width` CSS property sets an element's width. By default, it sets the width of the content area, but if box-sizing is set to border-box, it sets the width of the border area.
